You know, I support Narumitsu too, and do not like it either, but this is an actual real official play.

In the game canon, no. In the play canon, yes. That is what the note is for. Phoenix was also dating Leona Clyde (a renamed Lana Skye with the Edgeworth class trial backstory) in a different play, and Edgeworth even had one in another play. Eventually there will probably be an Phoenix-Edgeworth one. The Ace Attorney plays having added love interests all the time.

Iris was already mentioned in that list. Number one says Iris, and notes that she was impersonating her sister Dahlia when dating Phoenix. Her surname is also not Hawthorne; Dahlia had the Hawthorne family surname, but Iris did not. And Maya was a significant other in a stage play only, hence the note saying it was only in the stage play. Stage play-only love interests are relatively common, another one being Lana Skye (re-named ‘Leona Clyde’ and given Edgeworth’s old classroom trial backstory).
Concept art for the crossover and abandoned Edgeworth redesign.
